Available actions:
- observe_component: Visually inspect a component.
- measure_voltage: Measure voltage at component ports (w.r.t. ground) with a multimeter.
- measure_current: Measure the branch current through a component with a multimeter (ammeter mode).
- open_switch: Open a switch (set it to the off/open position). Safe to call even if already open.
- close_switch: Close a switch (set it to the on/closed position). Safe to call even if already closed.
- test_continuity: Measure resistance / continuity with a multimeter (ohmmeter mode).
- test_diode: Test a diode or LED forward voltage with a multimeter (diode-test mode).
- test_path_continuity: Measure the Thevenin resistance between a terminal of one component and a terminal of another (point-to-point continuity test).  params: {'source_port': 'str — port name on source component to probe (optional)', 'sink_port': 'str — port name on sink component to probe (optional)'}
- inspect_connections: Inspect which cables are physically connected to each port.
- invert_enclosure: Lift and invert an enclosure to look inside.
- restore_enclosure: Return an inverted enclosure to its normal orientation.
- rotate_enclosure: Rotate or move an enclosure to reposition it (e.g. break a line-of-sight coupling).
- open_peephole: Open a peephole to observe internal components.
- close_peephole: Close an open peephole.
- open_inspection_panel: Remove the inspection panel to access internal components for measurement.
- close_inspection_panel: Replace the inspection panel.
- replace_component: Replace a component with a new unit.  params: {'replacement_part_id': 'str — identifier of the replacement part', 'replacement_cost': 'float (default 1.0)'}
- adjust_potentiometer: Adjust the wiper position of a potentiometer.  params: {'new_position': 'float in [0.0, 1.0]'}
- verify_repair: Identify the component that the technician suspects is faulty and mark it for hypothesis verification (repair-and-test).
- move_led: Move a LED from its current module to another module LED slot. If the target slot already has a LED the two are swapped; if the target slot is empty the LED and its series resistor are moved.  params: {'target_module_id': "str — component_id of the target PhysicalEnclosure (e.g. 'cube_psu' or 'cube_ctrl3')"}
- short_ports: Bridge two component ports with a 0.01 Ω connection (models probing / wiring two circuit nodes together).  params: {'source_port': 'str — port name on source component to bridge (optional)', 'target_port': 'str — port name on sink component to bridge (optional)'}
- detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load: Detach a contiguous sequence of control modules (source = first module, sink = last module) from the circuit and connect them directly between PSU and load to test if the load lights up.

