name: Test -> control module output indicator LED and its drive circuitry,
description: With the system operating in the dark (so the relay should be commanded ON), observe the control module’s ‘switched cables indicator’ LED while the main lamp exhibits its 0.5 s outages. At the same time, measure the voltage between the control module’s output positive terminal and its local negative/return, and also measure the voltage directly across the indicator LED. Determine whether the indicator LED or the control‑module output voltage shows any fluctuation in sync with the main‑lamp dropouts, indicating that the control circuit is briefly modulating or current‑limiting the load path even though the relay contacts stay closed mechanically., outcome='The PSU Status LED (green) remains steadily lit with about 1.29 V across it and shows no indication of flicker or dropout.  \nThe control module’s output shows about 11.85 V on Control Output Cable (+) and near 0 V on Control Output Cable (−), with no reported fluctuation in sync with the main lamp outages.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
